1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ready?

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye.

3
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Breaking news!

4
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not so fast. Keep an eye out.

5
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey!

6
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please, Fajr.

7
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If Mum saw me having tea and biscuits,

8
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'd think I'd give in to hunger.

9
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're not going to University again.

10
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't even think about it!

11
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's my last semester.

12
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sorry! Mum's orders!

13
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No way you're getting out of here.

14
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can it!

15
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Told you! The game is on!

16
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I say,

17
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Instead of shouting or fighting back, just give in.

18
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Forget your studies.

19
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You off your head?

20
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
D'you know how much it'd cost me?

21
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what they all say.

22
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't think how much your decisions cost everyone.

23
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Shut up!

24
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You ought to bless me, Maheen!

25
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm the last ray of hope for your doomed love!

26
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Soooo sweet of you!</i>

27
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Done?

28
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not yet.

29
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum's here! Quick! Hide!

30
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Have something...

31
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What have we here?

32
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She hasn't had anything...

33
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good.

34
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good riddance of her

35
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If she starves herself to death!

36
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's got this awful headache for the last one hour!

37
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Big deal.

38
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We've all had an awful headache since last night.

39
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Out.

40
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Lemme massage her head, Mum!

41
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just do as you're told.

42
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And aye, where's the keys?

43
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Keys?

44
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why d'you need them?

45
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've been ordered to lock the room.

46
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Very good!

47
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Enough!

48
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The only out... Is a pall!

49
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Juliet's pall, I beg thee, must be most grand!</i>

50
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You blighter!

51
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And aye,

52
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're not going to University again.

53
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I will.

54
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even if I have to jump out the window.

55
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't know me, girl.

56
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm Ammi Begum's daughter.

57
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll char you with your obstinacy.

58
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Speaking of her...

59
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Could you tell Nano

60
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's making a big mistake

61
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
By taking up arms against love?

62
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Those who hate love will be blown to bits.

63
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At least have something before you go to bed, love, okay?

64
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ask him

65
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why he went with her.

66
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I didn't.

67
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She took me.

68
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As if he's a kid

69
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who lost his way and went with whoever held his hand!

70
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She was ashamed at what she did.

71
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just

72
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ashamed?

73
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So she'd kill and say sorry

74
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Because she's ashamed!

75
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who'd she kill?

76
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why, everyone standing there!

77
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wali,

78
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Me,

79
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You...!

80
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At long last you name the one who actually died.

81
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I didn't lose my life to her.

82
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They say you give your life for those who hold it dear.

83
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well said.

84
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wali,

85
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just tell him he's not seeing her again.

86
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why don't you say it?

87
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I think he understands.

88
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He won't see her again.

89
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good.

90
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Logically, after so much insult, I thought, too,

91
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That I'd never see her again.

92
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But she's a girl...

93
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And most like a girl...

94
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'd hide what lies in her heart so well

95
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She wouldn't have the foggiest herself!

96
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank goodness she found out.

97
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In fact, thank goodness she found out in time.

98
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm the only one insulted right now.

99
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Love's been spared the ignominy.

100
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wait.

101
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll go see.

102
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hi.

103
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're angry?

104
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Won't you let me in?

105
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please go back.

106
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're mourning the recent death of his heart.

107
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Praying for his soul.

108
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's best if the killer stayed at an arm's length.

109
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's this?

110
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
A lunchbox.

111
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's in it?

112
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Food.

113
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For?

114
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yours truly.

115
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ours, who?

116
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you think

117
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That makes no sense?

118
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It makes perfect sense to me.

119
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who you're about to give it to

120
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is truly not ours!

121
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You've started talking like Ammi Begum!

122
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He hasn't had anything since yesterday!

123
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He refused to order anything.

124
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The only thing he gets here is our wrath.

125
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Send him as much as you like.

126
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where does he live?

127
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can't tell you that.

128
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Whoa.

129
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You refuse to tell your masters?

130
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here.

131
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you doing?

132
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Way to go, Mehrunnisa!

133
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Could you be any more rebellious?

134
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You'd cook food with your own hands

135
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For the kids who've grown up to slander the family and bring it disgrace!

136
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I won't marry anyone else, Mehrunnisa!

137
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What was that?

138
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why'd you marry anyone else?

139
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
After you're gone, everyone's gonna ask me to.

140
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can turn them all down, but if Ammi Begum told me to...

141
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Get a grip on yourself, M. Dastoor.

142
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mehrunnisa

143
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ain't leaving you

144
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Behind.

145
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If Ammi Begum found out what you're up to,

146
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She'd kill you for real!

147
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She called me at work.

148
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Asked me to send her

149
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
New cartridges.

150
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If you don't want to be at the wrong end of the barrel,

151
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just let him starve to death!

152
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thought yourselves so clever, didn't you?

153
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ammi Begum was just outside, watching, hearing!

154
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you looking for?

155
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here's your lunchbox. Get going!

156
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Before the bugger starves to death!

157
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You better sit too.

158
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Spend your last few moments with me?

159
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are you looking at?

160
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Munshi Alam...

161
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I won't let him out of my sights.

162
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Follow me!

163
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Quickly!

164
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello?

165
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello, partner!

166
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Make it quick. I'm being watched!

167
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're sending him food.

168
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't tell me!

169
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've seen it myself! Munshi Alam packed a lunchbox for him!

170
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where does he live?

171
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll find out tomorrow.

172
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're following Munshi Alam.

173
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who's following him?

174
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ammi Begum!

175
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Although Mum and Dad think they're following him.

176
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't get it.

177
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Have you got a black suit?

178
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye.

179
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Maheen does too, I'm sure?

180
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye, but --

181
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Put it on.

182
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

183
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar ain't comin' back alive.

184
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Munshi Alam thought he could outfox us.

185
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How d'you like them apples now?

186
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll catch him red-handed,

187
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And drop the London tramp

188
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At the airport.

189
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hmm...

190
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What about Maheen?

191
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I mean, he was almost at the airport...

192
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Maheen called to stop him.

193
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If he deserves punishment for coming back,

194
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What about the one who stopped him?

195
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't worry. She won't be spared.

196
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's marrying Gulrez.

197
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At last...

198
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So you concede that marrying her off to Gulrez is a punishment.

199
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is that rebellion I catch a whiff of in your voice, Mehrunnisa?

200
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not just a whiff, M. Dastoor...

201
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
More like a rank stench,

202
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not of rebellion,

203
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But of the truth that rots in your heart as much as mine,

204
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And I'm sure

205
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ammi Begum's.

206
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Except she covers it up for the sake of Gulrez.

207
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Like anyone else her age, she thinks she can stop lovers.

208
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I dare her to!

209
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I wonder if you can say any of that to Ammi Begum's face...

210
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can.

211
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I'd rather you not marry someone else.

212
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But then...

213
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If not me, who?

214
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Could you?

215
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Before you get her the new cartridges,

216
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gather your courage and say it.

217
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
There!

218
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your pointless banter made me lose sight of Munshi Alam!

219
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No idea if he went right or left...

220
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Left.

221
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello?

222
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You alone?

223
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye.

224
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
HVT bagged!

225
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh, God...

226
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where?

227
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At the farmhouse.

228
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who bagged him?

229
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum, Dad, and Dado!

230
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Poor kid.

231
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll break the news and get back to you!

232
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay.

233
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello?

234
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bad news!

235
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah?

236
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's been done over.

237
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good!

238
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why do you 'good'-'very good' everything?

239
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm delighted!

240
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I mean,

241
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The world's changed,

242
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But not the loathing some people have for love!

243
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's always been this way.

244
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Two fall in love,

245
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And two hundred hate it!

246
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's how it is

247
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In 2008, as in 1908...

248
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Anyway, can't talk. Gotta write my diary!

249
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All my fault...

250
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I thought I could be friends with all...

251
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's cost me dearly...

252
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I raised all my kids with so much love...

253
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Only to see them grow into rebels...

254
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They hate

255
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And love who they want.

256
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Their love does not rest until it's quaffed the blood out of others' love...

257
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The quandary

258
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For my unfortunate self

259
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is that the one quaffing the blood

260
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is a piece of myself,

261
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And whose blood should he drink

262
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But the one

263
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who has a special place in my heart?

264
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How can you stay in one piece when parts of yourself go up in arms against each other, Waqar Ahmed?

265
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I heard the words of those who fear me just so they can please me.

266
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What did you say?

267
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Not just a whiff, M. Dastoor'...

268
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'More like the rank stench'

269
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Of the truth that rots'

270
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Inside you, as inside me',

271
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Hoping to get out someday',

272
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'As it does'

273
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Inside Ammi Begum, I'm sure',

274
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Except she covers it up'

275
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'For the sake of Gulrez Akhtar'...

276
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And also...

277
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Like everyone her age, Ammi Begum thinks she can stand in the way of lovers'...

278
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'I dare her to stop love if she's so powerful'!

279
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What do I tell you...

280
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If love could be stopped so easily,

281
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Elders like ourselves

282
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wouldn't be watching over you young'uns.

